Rheumatic fever is a severe inflammatory disease that can develop as a complication of untreated strep throat. The Rheumatic Fever Market is divided into several key segments based on products and end-users. Therapeutics form a significant part of the market, including medications used to manage symptoms and underlying infections. Diagnostics play a crucial role in identifying and monitoring the condition, encompassing lab tests, imaging techniques, and other tools for disease detection. End-users of rheumatic fever products and services include hospitals, clinics, diagnostic centers, and research institutions.

